[[File:Бикин, верховья.jpg|thumb|300px|Bikin river]]

'''Bikin''' ({{lang-ru|Бики́н}}) is a river in [[Primorsky Krai|Primorsky]] and [[Khabarovsk Krai]]s in [[Russia]]. It is a right tributary of the [[Ussuri River]], and is {{convert|560|km|mi}} long, with a [[drainage basin]] of {{convert|22300|km2|mi2}}.

Its main tributaries are the [[Alchan River|Alchan]], [[Bachelaza River|Bachelaza]] and [[Zeva River|Zeva]] rivers.

The town [[Bikin]] is situated on the Bikin River.

In 2015, a significant portion of the Bikin River basin was incorporated into the creation of [[Bikin National Park]], one of the major protected areas of the Russian Federation.

